# Prometheus Monitoring

<%= baseName %> includes built-in Prometheus metrics support for monitoring application performance and health.

## Overview

The application exposes metrics at `/management/prometheus` in the standard Prometheus text format. These metrics are automatically collected by the `axum-prometheus` middleware.

## Available Metrics

### HTTP Request Metrics

| Metric | Type | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `axum_http_requests_total` | Counter | Total number of HTTP requests, labeled by method, path, and status |
| `axum_http_requests_duration_seconds` | Histogram | HTTP request duration distribution |
| `axum_http_requests_pending` | Gauge | Number of currently in-flight requests |

### Labels

All HTTP metrics include the following labels:

- `method`: HTTP method (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, etc.)
- `path`: Request path (normalized)
- `status`: HTTP status code

## Configuration

### Environment Variables

| Variable | Description | Default |
|----------|-------------|---------|
| `METRICS_ENABLED` | Enable/disable metrics collection | `true` |
| `METRICS_PATH` | Path for metrics endpoint | `/management/prometheus` |

### Example Configuration

```bash
# Enable metrics (default)
METRICS_ENABLED=true

# Disable metrics for production if not needed
METRICS_ENABLED=false
```

